<exercise checkit-seed="0002" checkit-slug="AppDiffEVT" checkit-title="Extreme Value Theorem">
    <statement>
        <p> 
Explain how to find the absolute minimum and absolute maximum values of the
function <m>f(x)=2 \, x^{3} + 36 \, x^{2} + 192 \, x - 51</m> on the interval <m>[-6,0]</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
The absolute extrema may occur at these <m>x</m>-values:
<m>-6, -4, 0</m>.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><p><m>f(-6)=-339</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(-4)=-371</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(0)=-51</m></p></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
Thus the absolute minimum is <m>-371</m> and the absolute
maximum is <m>-51</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
(The value <m>f(-8)=-307</m>
is ignored as <m>-8</m> isn't in the given interval.)
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
